			<ns0:name>halya...@google.com</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/112856509894568708731/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">I found that new versions of Windows implement POSIX-like synchronization primitives.
Conditional variables are available starting from Windows Vista: http://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/windows/desktop/ms687080(v=vs.85).aspx

Futexes are available starting from Windows 8:
http://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/windows/desktop/hh706898(v=vs.85).aspx

May be we can use those to create faster paths for new Windows versions.</ns0:content><ns0:updated>2013-06-09T12:49:32.000Z</ns0:updated><ns0:published>2013-06-09T12:49:32.000Z</ns0:published><ns2:updates /><ns0:title>Comment 4 by halya...@google.com</ns0:title><ns0:link href="http://code.google.com/p/nativeclient/issues/detail?id=1244#c4" rel="alternate" type="text/html" /><ns0:link href="https://code.google.com/feeds/issues/p/nativeclient/issues/1244/comments/full/4" rel="self" type="application/atom+xml" /></ns0:entry>